benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to bundle

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC16, @TC19, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25 cover successful modifications with valid headers and bodies.
Empty Response: @TC03 covers removal of all custom fields (empty array).
Non-Existing Resource: @TC05 covers bundle not found (404).
Invalid bundleId format: @TC04 covers invalid bundleId format (400).
Missing required header: @TC06 covers missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy (400).
Malformed JSON body: @TC07 covers malformed JSON (400).
Missing request body: @TC08 covers missing body (400).
Extra, unsupported parameters: @TC16 covers URL with unexpected query parameters (204).
Unauthorized access: @TC10 covers missing auth token (401).
Service unavailable: @TC11 covers dependency/service unavailability (503).
Security - SQL injection: @TC12 covers injection attempt (400).
Maximum allowed custom fields: @TC13 covers boundary condition for max custom fields.
Maximum value length: @TC14 covers boundary for custom field value length.
Empty custom field value: @TC15 covers empty string in custom field.
Special characters: @TC19 covers special characters in custom fields.
Inconsistent data: @TC20 covers internal server error scenario.
Transient network failure: @TC21 covers retry logic.
Bundle with no existing custom fields: @TC22 covers creation scenario.
Partial update: @TC24 covers partial matching and updates.
Backward compatibility: @TC25 covers older client versions.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Concurrency issues: No explicit tests for race conditions during concurrent updates.
Response content validation: No detailed validation of response bodies beyond status codes.
Edge cases for unsupported custom field types or invalid data formats beyond injection.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling to verify proper response with large datasets.
Include rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure system stability under load.
Implement tests for caching headers to verify proper cache control and validation.
Create concurrency tests to detect race conditions during simultaneous updates.
Enhance validation of response bodies to ensure data integrity and correctness.
Test unsupported custom field types and invalid data formats for robustness.
